    "body": "I like the anonymity aspect of it and the plausible deniability aspect. Perhaps it should be a setting for random names determined by address to pop up and from there allow for people to change the name client side themselves. No need to be broadcasting your identity to certain accounts. Or better yet, compress identity into an encrypted whisper packet, and from there open it alongside the first message to give you...the identity described...problem is this could lead to some nasty scammers...Uport comes to mind for some assertion of identity here. ",
